t against the total machinery of world as an enslaving system, the instrument of punishment + the source of ineluctable tragedy + human helplessness in which man is a captive of the world into which he has been thrown - under his which conditions not even -especially!- death is his (Eigen). These are radically opposite (1801) ways of Dasein: victim of world (while maintaining a lofter, noble, aristocratic stance) or hero confronting + overcoming world-a‐ Fate (while posing as sacrifice, which worlds \"swallows\" as bait). In both cases (modes) the ostensible + the actual are opposites of each other: the King succumbs; the slave trumphs. we are here not merely at the heart of Xtianity - at its true secret - but at the heart of 1) how one truly is victor in + vis-a-vis world; + 2) why everything is 1800 opposite to what it ostensibly seems to be, + 3) the modern world versus the ancient: the modern (that C-207 is, from the first advent on how man now wins, whereas before the first advent he lost, he lost grandly but still was doomed to lose; he now wins in a gentle + meek way yet truly wins: a little winning is better than a lot of losing + s all this is the transformation that Christ has brought us. + in the Tagore vision his (Christ's + hence our) victory i s complete: the eschatological predictions are fulfilled in + as this vision: this is the form that true victory takes (once you know the 180Â° \"mirror reversal\" coaxial system in which ostensible victory is grand tragedy - defect - + osten sible sacrifice is small but real - + now total - victory. Total victory \"by the Light\" must take the Form I saw in my Tagore vision; I understand that now. Armies of warrior angels + a stern eschatological judge + king would be the ostensible \"victory\" of antiquity which was actually grand defeat However, in covert - muted - actuality Tagore is the eschatological judge who sentences us as a species + a planet to doom if we do not repent, but he does so as sacrifice, martyr, wounded & dying - + forced to with draw from world - in defeat. No; in [true but concealed] victory; it is we who as the evil ones of world are defeated; the light successfully unmixes + withdraws the vision of the second Advent as the suffering & dying self-sacrificing Tagore could not be other than it is, because now if + when he withdraws he takes -203 with him the spirit of the world itself; thus in a covert sense he has power over - which is to say rules - all life: the ecosphere as a having whole, being now identical with it - assimilated it to himself upon his original act of invading it. the weapons of power - coercive physical power - lose because then inevitably encounter some adversary more powerful. The only real victory can occur by being conquered (as bait/sacrifice: swallowed by evil) + then coming-into-being at the center of evil, + this is precisely what true Xtianity - in secret has done; thus it is subversive + invisible at the center of power in its disguised form i.e. to evil, (mimesis). Evil poses as good; good invisible within it, unknown to it i the BIP). All this is taught in the \"Tao Te Ching,\" oddly: this is how the Tao works \"a perturbation in the reality field\"). note: \"Evil, which is in power, poses as good.\" this is the BIP, both church + state. But good does not, conversely, pose as evil; \"good is invisible secretly at the heart of evil, trans‐ forming -i.e. subverting it\" - + this is what they do not pose as saw: the true secret Xtians + their \"protess\" anything at all: they are invisible by way of information (plasmate). I an uncanny mimicry. (mimesis.) Since we ostensibly experience evil as good the logic of a \"secret good\" hidden at its heart, 1800 the opposite of it makes no logical sense - but if the ostensible good (which rules) is correctly seen as evil, it does make sense - or, which is how it worked with me, suddenly o - as seeing the covent good causes the percipient at once to reverse his understanding of 